column37: It should at least have the features mentioned above. I prefer if the teacher and students all turn on video to retain classroom atmosphere. There should be only one app doing all these tasks. I hate having to use multiple apps and multiple accounts, so much problem remembering passwords. The Notification IS MUST. Notification for whatever reason like deadlines, details, instructions for assignments and AT THE LEAST FOR When on What Time Date the next meeting will be, should be sent on our phones, Otherwise we don't even know that its class at 8 :30 am and we are waking up at 11:00am. The biggest problem was that some teachers had a really BAD TIME MANAGEMENT OR (BETTER TO SAY) NO TIME SCHEDULE, THE RESULT WAS WE WERE SUFFERING HAVING TO LISTEN LECTURES AT 9:00 - 10:00PM AT NIGHT. IN THE BEGINNING WE EVEN HAD TWO CONTINOUS CONSECUTIVE DAYS OF CLASSES. It was Monday and Tuesday when this happened and just two days ago on Friday we were told about lock down. What happened on Monday and Tuesday was a disaster. We had all theory classes from 10:30 to 12:00, then 12:00 to 2:30, simultaneously a really interuptive class at another app 1:30-3:30, during this 2:30-4:00 a Google classroom account making, instructions for assignments blah blah which I guess none of us took interest in, since we were occupied with our class,then were told to submit an assignment based on all the course covered until now. All night spent on assignment till 10:00 in the Tuesday morning. Most Submitted by 10:30 although 9:00 was the decided deadline. Then classes again from 10:30 - 12-30 & then 12:39 - 3:00 and then again working on new assignments and tasks. All cramped up the same like this for the next two weeks as well
